{
  "question_id": "2e82702c-016c-4c4a-8220-b756e58ef02b",
  "short_text": "Numbers in Inverted Right Angled Triangle",
  "content": "Given a number `N`, write a program to print an **Inverted Right Angled Triangle** of `N` rows using numbers starting from **1**.\r\n\r\n```\r\n1 2 3 4\r\n1 2 3\r\n1 2\r\n1\r\n```\r\n\r\n<MultiLineNote>\r\nThere is a space after every number.\r\n</MultiLineNote>\r\n\r\n#### Input\r\n\r\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Output\r\n\r\nThe output should be `N` rows containing numbers starting from **1** as an **Inverted Right Angled Triangle** shown in the sample output.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Explanation\r\n\r\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 5`,\r\n\r\n- Print the numbers on **5** rows as shown in the given image.\r\n\r\n<Img imageSrc='https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/cx-numbers-in-inverted-right-angled-triangle.png' widthPercent='100'/>\r\n\r\n<MultiLineNote>\r\n\r\nIn the given image,\r\n\r\n- The Number in box indicates the number and a space (\"1 \")\r\n\r\n</MultiLineNote>\r\n\r\nThe output should be,\r\n\r\n```\r\n1 2 3 4 5\r\n1 2 3 4\r\n1 2 3\r\n1 2\r\n1\r\n```",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "4ebde5b6-9de0-4341-b1db-46706d89be4d",
      "code_content": "n = int(input())\n\nfor row in range(n):\n    each_row = \"\"\n    numbers_in_row = n - row\n    for number in range(1, numbers_in_row + 1):\n        each_row = each_row + (str(number) + \" \")\n\n    print(each_row)",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
